{"id":10,"actions":[{"skillId":1,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0},{"skillId":35,"rating":6,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0},{"skillId":71,"rating":7,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0}],"battlerHue":0,"battlerName":"Battle Sprites/NunoSaPunso-Enemy","dropItems":[{"dataId":1,"denominator":1,"kind":0},{"dataId":1,"denominator":1,"kind":0},{"dataId":1,"denominator":1,"kind":0}],"exp":200,"traits":[{"code":22,"dataId":0,"value":0.95},{"code":22,"dataId":1,"value":0.05},{"code":31,"dataId":1,"value":0}],"gold":300,"name":"Nuno sa punso","note":"<Bestiary Lore>\n<WordWrap>The nuno sa punso are known to inflict illness on people who dare to disturb their dwelling place. Common punishments for the offenders include high fever, body pain, and swollen genitals (for peeing on their anthill). Suspected victims of the nuno sa punso are advised to seek help from an albularyo, a practitioner of traditional medicine.\n</Bestiary Lore>","params":[1200,0,25,30,25,120,18,10]},
{"id":11,"actions":[{"skillId":4,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0},{"skillId":40,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0},{"skillId":124,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0},{"skillId":31,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0}],"battlerHue":0,"battlerName":"Battle Sprites/Syokoy-Enemy BIG","dropItems":[{"kind":1,"dataId":45,"denominator":40},{"kind":1,"dataId":11,"denominator":25},{"dataId":1,"denominator":1,"kind":0}],"exp":1000,"traits":[{"code":22,"dataId":0,"value":0.95},{"code":22,"dataId":1,"value":0.05},{"code":31,"dataId":1,"value":0}],"gold":450,"name":"Syokoy","note":"<Bestiary Lore>\n<WordWrap>In Philippine mythology, a siyokoy (also syokoy or siokoy) is an aquatic humanoid creature often described as having scales, webbed limbs, and fins. Most legends characterise siyokoy as hostile to humans, and are said to drown individuals.\n</Bestiary Lore>","params":[4000,0,40,55,30,15,22,10]},
{"id":12,"actions":[{"skillId":4,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0},{"skillId":26,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0},{"skillId":31,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0},{"skillId":123,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0},{"skillId":126,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0}],"battlerHue":0,"battlerName":"Battle Sprites/Sirena-Enemy","dropItems":[{"kind":1,"dataId":41,"denominator":45},{"kind":1,"dataId":11,"denominator":25},{"dataId":1,"denominator":1,"kind":0}],"exp":1200,"traits":[{"code":22,"dataId":0,"value":0.95},{"code":22,"dataId":1,"value":0.05},{"code":31,"dataId":1,"value":0}],"gold":200,"name":"Sirena","note":"<Bestiary Lore>\n<WordWrap>Sirena are a captivating group in Filipino mythology. They are seen as beautiful women with fish tails. These creatures live in the deep waters around the Philippines. The myths highlight their attractive voices that lure fishermen. The Sirena’s songs can lead sailors to danger. They have a human upper body and a fish tail, like mermaids.\n</Bestiary Lore>","params":[2500,0,40,50,40,120,25,10]},
{"id":13,"actions":[{"skillId":4,"rating":5,"conditionType":0,"conditionParam1":0,"conditionParam2":0}],"battlerHue":0,"battlerName":"Battle Sprites/Mananaggal-Enemy","dropItems":[{"kind":1,"dataId":10,"denominator":15},{"kind":1,"dataId":14,"denominator":30},{"dataId":1,"denominator":1,"kind":0}],"exp":300,"traits":[{"code":22,"dataId":0,"value":0.95},{"code":22,"dataId":1,"value":0.05},{"code":31,"dataId":1,"value":0}],"gold":250,"name":"Manananggal","note":"<Bestiary Lore>\n<WordWrap>Manananggal is a mythical creature in Philippine folklore that has been passed down through generations. It is a terrifying and powerful creature that can detach its upper body from its lower half and fly at night to feed on human blood. The word “manananggal” comes from the Tagalog word “tanggal,” which means “to remove” or “to separate,” which literally translates as “remover” or “separator.”\n</Bestiary Lore>","params":[2500,0,30,50,40,50,30,10]},
